description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a newly qualified &lt;strong&gt;Registered Mental Health / Learning Disability Nurse (RMN/ RNLD)&lt;/strong&gt; to complete their Preceptorship programme at our Acute / Autism Spectrum Disorder Servicein London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be working 38.5 hours per week at &lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Hospital Harrow,&lt;/strong&gt; located in Harrow on the Hill.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Hospital Harrow&lt;/strong&gt; provides a recovery focused service treating a wide range of mental health problems. We also offer specialist diagnostic, assessment and inpatient services for individuals with mental health needs and who also have a dual diagnosis of autism spectrum disorder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to enjoy excellent career prospects whilereaping the rewards of making a difference to others – every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your programme includes...&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Support from Cygnet’s Preceptorship Development Manager&lt;br /&gt;• Minimum two shifts per week working with your nominated preceptor&lt;br /&gt;• Preceptee supernumery 1st week on ward&lt;br /&gt;• Monthly CPD Days off the ward (specialist and general)&lt;br /&gt;• Clinical supervision, minimum 1 session per month&lt;br /&gt;• Managerial supervision, minimum 1 session per month&lt;br /&gt;• Preceptee Group Meetings on site and across the Cygnet group&lt;br /&gt;• Certificate and letter of completion&lt;br /&gt;• Excellent training opportunities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An action plan will then be created by you and your preceptor for the following six months to enhance identified strengths and address areas of development, taking you to your first annual appraisal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Open, compassionate, honest &amp; resilient&lt;br /&gt;•Newly Qualified Learning Disability or Mental Health Nurse&lt;br /&gt;•Capable to maintain documentation and undertake audits&lt;br /&gt;•Well informed of the Mental Health Act 1983 &amp; have an understanding of latest nursing practices&lt;br /&gt;•Able to deputise in a clinical lead role&lt;br /&gt;•Focused on patient recovery to monitor, manage &amp; reduce risk&lt;br /&gt;•Helping to empower &amp; support service user independence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•£12.22 per hour (£24,400 pa)plus enhancements&lt;br /&gt;• + £4,000 Location Allowance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•Enhancement rates;&lt;br /&gt; 10% of basic Salary for Night shifts&lt;br /&gt; 20% of basic salary for weekend shifts&lt;br /&gt; 30% of basic rate for nights on the weekend&lt;br /&gt; 66% of basic rate for bank holidays&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% of NMC registration renewal paid byCygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous study and exam leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Teaching and CPD Programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Financial support for further training and personal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty and free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monthly reflective practice, support with revalidation &amp; CPD opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert clinical supervision &amp; peer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee discount savings &amp; “Cycle to work” scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bespoke career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plus many more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cygnet Health Care has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for 30 years&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location Information:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Hospital Harrow&lt;/strong&gt; provides a recovery focused service treating a wide range of mental health problems. We also offer specialist diagnostic, assessment and inpatient services for individuals with mental health needs and who also have a dual diagnosis of autism spectrum disorder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A newly qualified nurse, you’ll engage in a period of preceptorship during your first six months of employment, ensuring your career receives the best possible start. Offering flexibility to accommodate individual needs, Cygnet Healthcare will help to prepare you for your professional role and encourage best practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What next?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you care about making a difference – we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click the link to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
